Claude started playing rugby league in Queensland at the age of 10 and continued in New Zealand, playing for Kingsland Rovers from 1921. He moved to the 2nd grade side in 1923 and won the 2nd grade knockout competition in 1924. He made his senior debut for Kingsland in the B Division in 1925, becoming one of the only players to gain selection for Auckland from that grade. He scored multiple tries in his first matches and was selected for the Auckland Junior representative side, playing on the wing and scoring a try in their win against Hamilton juniors. His successful 1925 season led to his selection for the national side in 1928, becoming the first ever player in New Zealand to be selected from a second division side.
